OL,3,C'We've got to listen to the community'
OL,4,C- one year since the Cwmtillery
OL,5,Clandslip
OL,7,FIt's been one year since dozens of
OL,8,Fpeople in Cwmtillery, Blaenau Gwent,
OL,9,Fwere forced from their homes
OL,10,Fovernight, as mud and water came up to
OL,11,Ftheir windows following Storm Bert.
OL,13,FThe Welsh Government confirmed at the
OL,14,Ftime that it was a landslip caused by
OL,15,Fa "singular wash-out of former coal
OL,16,Ftip in the area."
OL,18,FDeputy First Minister Huw Irranca-
OL,19,FDavies returned to Cwmtillery this
OL,20,Fweek, reflecting on the memory of the
OL,21,Fevent.
