OL,3,C'We've got to listen to the community'
OL,4,C- one year since the Cwmtillery
OL,5,Clandslip
OL,7,F"The scenes from Cwmtillery last year
OL,8,Fwill always stay with me," he said.
OL,9,F"Returning to Cwmtillery twelve months
OL,10,Fon, I'm pleased to see the substantial
OL,11,Fprogress made to support this
OL,12,Fcommunity and make the site safer."
OL,14,FMr Irranca-Davies reaffirmed the Welsh
OL,15,FGovernment's commitment to long-term
OL,16,Fsafety. "We remain absolutely
OL,17,Fdedicated to protecting people and
OL,18,Fensuring communities living in the
OL,19,Fshadow of former tips are safe, both
OL,20,Fnow and in the future," he added.
